snippet.textDisplay: Rob, I haven't always been your biggest fan because you sometimes seem more focused on how you'll be perceived than on the build. This video - especially just after the burnout - is pure, emotional, real, and the exact opposite of that. Congratulations on this build, and massive respect for having the self-confidence to be vulnerable in public. Thank you for sharing your joy and overwhelm with us. That experience - that fear leading up to the thing, that adrenaline rush of doing it, and that massive fucking dopamine hit afterwards - is why we build interesting cars, and it's why we like to watch other people do it. Nice work. You earned every bit of that joy and adrenaline. This is an amazing car. You and your crew have done an amazing thing.
